The paper discusses the reactive programming style, which is a programming paradigm that deals with events and their reactions. This falls under the category of programming languages (cs.PL) and software engineering (cs.SE). The paper also discusses concurrency, which falls under the category of distributed, parallel, and cluster computing (cs.DC) and data structures and algorithms (cs.DS). Finally, the paper outlines some questions that remain to be investigated, which could fall under the category of logic in computer science (cs.LO).
